President Joe Biden and Prime Minister Narendra Modi of India had a phone conversation where they discussed various issues. They pledged to work closely together to combat the COVID-19 pandemic and renew their partnership on climate change. They also expressed their commitment to rebuilding the global economy in a way that benefits both countries and standing united against global terrorism. The leaders agreed to promote a free and open Indo-Pacific region, including supporting freedom of navigation and territorial integrity. They also emphasized the importance of democratic values and the rule of law, particularly in Burma. Both leaders expressed their intention to stay in close communication and work together on global challenges.